+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Gppam9DtdVgz4mXeE13mS4","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good. The project scaffolding is in place (package.json, tsconfig, vitest config) but `src/` is empty. Now I'll work through the design decisions in autopilot mode.\n\n**Design Decisions:**\n\n**Q1: Overall architecture — monolithic class vs modular components?**\n→ Choosing: **Modular components** with a facade `Spreadsheet` class\n  Reasoning: Separate concerns (parsing, evaluation, dependency tracking) into distinct modules for testability and clarity, but expose a single `Spreadsheet` class as the public API.\n\n**Q2: Formula parser approach — hand-written recursive descent vs library?**\n→ Choosing: **Hand-written recursive descent parser**\n  Reasoning: No external dependencies needed. The grammar is simple enough (arithmetic expressions, function calls, cell references, ranges). A recursive descent parser handles operator precedence cleanly.\n\n**Q3: Dependency tracking — eager recomputation vs lazy?**\n→ Choosing: **Eager recomputation** via topological sort\n  Reasoning: When a cell changes, immediately recompute all dependents in topological order. This ensures `get()` is always O(1) — just a lookup. The spreadsheet is write-heavy but read-heavy too, and eager updates match user expectations.\n\n**Q4: Circular reference detection approach?**\n→ Choosing: **DFS cycle detection during `set()`**\n  Reasoning: When a formula is set, parse its dependencies, then run DFS on the dependency graph to check for cycles before accepting the formula. Throw an error and reject the change if a cycle is found.\n\n**Q5: Cell reference parsing — regex vs parser integration?**\n→ Choosing: **Integrated into the recursive descent parser**\n  Reasoning: Cell references and ranges are tokens in the grammar. The lexer identifies them, and the parser handles them as primary expressions or range expressions in function arguments.\n\n**Q6: Module structure?**\n→ Choosing:\n- `src/index.ts` — Spreadsheet class (public API, re-export)\n- `src/parser.ts` — Tokenizer + recursive descent parser → AST\n- `src/evaluator.ts` — AST evaluation with cell lookups\n- `src/types.ts` — Shared types (AST nodes, cell value types)\n\nDesign complete. Made 6 decisions:\n\n1. Modular components with Spreadsheet facade\n2. Hand-written recursive descent parser\n3. Eager recomputation via topological sort\n4. DFS cycle detection on set()\n5. Cell refs integrated in parser\n6. 4-file module structure\n\nNow let me write the design document and proceed to planning."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":295,"cache_read_input_tokens":23420,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":295},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ebcc5083-d38a-4396-a837-b922d420a8c3","uuid":"c1b51721-08b5-4d4e-8505-a6618ef10097"}
