+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019Nr383CB7aWatqeFmtf3s9","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Reactive Spreadsheet Engine Design\n     2→\n     3→## Architecture\n     4→\n     5→Modular components behind a `Spreadsheet` facade class.\n     6→\n     7→### Modules\n     8→\n     9→1. **`src/types.ts`** — Shared types: AST node types, cell value types, token types\n    10→2. **`src/parser.ts`** — Tokenizer + recursive descent parser producing an AST\n    11→3. **`src/evaluator.ts`** — Evaluates AST nodes given a cell-value lookup function\n    12→4. **`src/index.ts`** — `Spreadsheet` class: cell storage, dependency graph, reactive updates, public API\n    13→\n    14→### Formula Grammar\n    15→\n    16→```\n    17→expression  → comparison\n    18→comparison  → addition (( \">\" | \"<\" | \">=\" | \"<=\" | \"=\" | \"<>\" ) addition)*\n    19→addition    → multiplication (( \"+\" | \"-\" ) multiplication)*\n    20→multiplication → unary (( \"*\" | \"/\" ) unary)*\n    21→unary       → \"-\" unary | primary\n    22→primary     → NUMBER | STRING | BOOLEAN | CELL_REF | function_call | \"(\" expression \")\"\n    23→function_call → IDENTIFIER \"(\" arg_list \")\"\n    24→arg_list    → (expression | range) (\",\" (expression | range))*\n    25→range       → CELL_REF \":\" CELL_REF\n    26→```\n    27→\n    28→### Dependency Tracking\n    29→\n    30→- Each cell stores its parsed AST and set of dependency cell references.\n    31→- A reverse dependency map tracks which cells depend on a given cell.\n    32→- On `set()`: parse formula → extract dependencies → check for cycles (DFS) → store → recompute dependents in topological order.\n    33→\n    34→### Circular Reference Detection\n    35→\n    36→- DFS from the cell being set, following forward dependencies.\n    37→- If the DFS revisits the cell being set, a cycle exists → throw error, reject change.\n    38→\n    39→### Cell Reference Parsing\n    40→\n    41→- Column letters converted to 0-based index: A=0, B=1, ..., Z=25, AA=26, etc.\n    42→- Row numbers converted to 0-based index internally.\n    43→- Ranges expand to list of cell references covering the rectangular region.\n    44→\n    45→### Data Flow\n    46→\n    47→1. `set(ref, value)` → parse if formula → extract deps → cycle check → store → topo-sort dependents → recompute each\n    48→2. `get(ref)` → return stored computed value (O(1))\n    49→3. `getDisplay(ref)` → return string representation of computed value\n    50→4. `getCells()` → return Map of all non-empty cells with computed values\n    51→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ebcc5083-d38a-4396-a837-b922d420a8c3","uuid":"0fad76b1-5a13-4d46-a4ef-52388073dcea","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-reactive-spreadsheet-design.md","content":"# Reactive Spreadsheet Engine Design\n\n## Architecture\n\nModular components behind a `Spreadsheet` facade class.\n\n### Modules\n\n1. **`src/types.ts`** — Shared types: AST node types, cell value types, token types\n2. **`src/parser.ts`** — Tokenizer + recursive descent parser producing an AST\n3. **`src/evaluator.ts`** — Evaluates AST nodes given a cell-value lookup function\n4. **`src/index.ts`** — `Spreadsheet` class: cell storage, dependency graph, reactive updates, public API\n\n### Formula Grammar\n\n```\nexpression  → comparison\ncomparison  → addition (( \">\" | \"<\" | \">=\" | \"<=\" | \"=\" | \"<>\" ) addition)*\naddition    → multiplication (( \"+\" | \"-\" ) multiplication)*\nmultiplication → unary (( \"*\" | \"/\" ) unary)*\nunary       → \"-\" unary | primary\nprimary     → NUMBER | STRING | BOOLEAN | CELL_REF | function_call | \"(\" expression \")\"\nfunction_call → IDENTIFIER \"(\" arg_list \")\"\narg_list    → (expression | range) (\",\" (expression | range))*\nrange       → CELL_REF \":\" CELL_REF\n```\n\n### Dependency Tracking\n\n- Each cell stores its parsed AST and set of dependency cell references.\n- A reverse dependency map tracks which cells depend on a given cell.\n- On `set()`: parse formula → extract dependencies → check for cycles (DFS) → store → recompute dependents in topological order.\n\n### Circular Reference Detection\n\n- DFS from the cell being set, following forward dependencies.\n- If the DFS revisits the cell being set, a cycle exists → throw error, reject change.\n\n### Cell Reference Parsing\n\n- Column letters converted to 0-based index: A=0, B=1, ..., Z=25, AA=26, etc.\n- Row numbers converted to 0-based index internally.\n- Ranges expand to list of cell references covering the rectangular region.\n\n### Data Flow\n\n1. `set(ref, value)` → parse if formula → extract deps → cycle check → store → topo-sort dependents → recompute each\n2. `get(ref)` → return stored computed value (O(1))\n3. `getDisplay(ref)` → return string representation of computed value\n4. `getCells()` → return Map of all non-empty cells with computed values\n","numLines":51,"startLine":1,"totalLines":51}}}
