+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01BHJJciiaDzWToGR44JrpM3","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01KG6b7sf3ahaquLWUieobYL","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-reactive-spreadsheet-plan.md","content":"# Reactive Spreadsheet Engine Implementation Plan\n\n> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use conclave:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.\n\n**Goal:** Build a TypeScript spreadsheet engine with formula parsing, reactive dependency tracking, and built-in functions.\n\n**Architecture:** Modular design with 4 source files: types (AST/token types), parser (tokenizer + recursive descent), evaluator (AST evaluation), and index (Spreadsheet facade class with dependency graph). Eager recomputation via topological sort on cell change.\n\n**Tech Stack:** TypeScript 5.4+, Vitest 2.0, ESM modules (Node16 module resolution)\n\n---\n\n### Task 0: Install Dependencies\n\n**Files:** none (project setup)\n\n**Dependencies:** none\n\n**Step 1: Install npm dependencies**\n\nRun: `cd /workspace && npm install`\nExpected: All devDependencies installed successfully.\n\n**Step 2: Verify tooling works**\n\nRun: `npx tsc --version && npx vitest --version`\nExpected: TypeScript and Vitest version numbers printed.\n\n**Step 3: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add -A && git commit -m \"chore: install dependencies\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 1: Types Module\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/types.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 0\n\n**Step 1: Create the types file**\n\nCreate `src/types.ts` with these types:\n\n```typescript\n// Token types for the lexer\nexport enum TokenType {\n  Number,\n  String,\n  Boolean,\n  CellRef,\n  Identifier,\n  Plus,\n  Minus,\n  Star,\n  Slash,\n  LParen,\n  RParen,\n  Comma,\n  Colon,\n  Gt,\n  Lt,\n  Gte,\n  Lte,\n  Eq,\n  Neq,\n  EOF,\n}\n\nexport interface Token {\n  type: TokenType;\n  value: string;\n}\n\n// AST node types\nexport type ASTNode =\n  | NumberLiteral\n  | StringLiteral\n  | BooleanLiteral\n  | CellRefNode\n  | BinaryOp\n  | UnaryOp\n  | FunctionCall\n  | RangeNode;\n\nexport interface NumberLiteral {\n  kind: 'number';\n  value: number;\n}\n\nexport interface StringLiteral {\n  kind: 'string';\n  value: string;\n}\n\nexport interface BooleanLiteral {\n  kind: 'boolean';\n  value: boolean;\n}\n\nexport interface CellRefNode {\n  kind: 'cellref';\n  ref: string; // e.g. \"A1\", normalized to uppercase\n}\n\nexport interface BinaryOp {\n  kind: 'binary';\n  op: string;\n  left: ASTNode;\n  right: ASTNode;\n}\n\nexport interface UnaryOp {\n  kind: 'unary';\n  op: string;\n  operand: ASTNode;\n}\n\nexport interface FunctionCall {\n  kind: 'function';\n  name: string;\n  args: ASTNode[];\n}\n\nexport interface RangeNode {\n  kind: 'range';\n  start: string; // e.g. \"A1\"\n  end: string;   // e.g. \"A5\"\n}\n\n// Cell value type\nexport type CellValue = string | number | boolean | null;\n```\n\n**Step 2: Verify it compiles**\n\nRun: `npx tsc --noEmit`\nExpected: No errors.\n\n**Step 3: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/types.ts && git commit -m \"feat: add shared types for AST, tokens, and cell values\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Parser Module\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/parser.ts`\n- Create: `src/__tests__/parser.test.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 1\n\n**Step 1: Write parser tests**\n\nCreate `src/__tests__/parser.test.ts`:\n\n```typescript\nimport { describe, it, expect } from 'vitest';\nimport { parse } from '../parser.js';\n\ndescribe('Parser', () => {\n  describe('literals', () => {\n    it('parses numbers', () => {\n      expect(parse('42')).toEqual({ kind: 'number', value: 42 });\n    });\n\n    it('parses decimal numbers', () => {\n      expect(parse('3.14')).toEqual({ kind: 'number', value: 3.14 });\n    });\n\n    it('parses strings', () => {\n      expect(parse('\"hello\"')).toEqual({ kind: 'string', value: 'hello' });\n    });\n\n    it('parses booleans', () => {\n      expect(parse('true')).toEqual({ kind: 'boolean', value: true });\n      expect(parse('false')).toEqual({ kind: 'boolean', value: false });\n    });\n  });\n\n  describe('cell references', () => {\n    it('parses simple cell ref', () => {\n      expect(parse('A1')).toEqual({ kind: 'cellref', ref: 'A1' });\n    });\n\n    it('parses multi-letter column', () => {\n      expect(parse('AA10')).toEqual({ kind: 'cellref', ref: 'AA10' });\n    });\n\n    it('normalizes to uppercase', () => {\n      expect(parse('a1')).toEqual({ kind: 'cellref', ref: 'A1' });\n    });\n  });\n\n  describe('arithmetic', () => {\n    it('parses addition', () => {\n      const ast = parse('A1+B1');\n      expect(ast).toEqual({\n        kind: 'binary',\n        op: '+',\n        left: { kind: 'cellref', ref: 'A1' },\n        right: { kind: 'cellref', ref: 'B1' },\n      });\n    });\n\n    it('respects operator precedence', () => {\n      const ast = parse('A1+B1*2');\n      expect(ast).toEqual({\n        kind: 'binary',\n        op: '+',\n        left: { kind: 'cellref', ref: 'A1' },\n        right: {\n          kind: 'binary',\n          op: '*',\n          left: { kind: 'cellref', ref: 'B1' },\n          right: { kind: 'number', value: 2 },\n        },\n      });\n    });\n\n    it('handles parentheses', () => {\n      const ast = parse('(A1+B1)*2');\n      expect(ast).toEqual({\n        kind: 'binary',\n        op: '*',\n        left: {\n          kind: 'binary',\n          op: '+',\n          left: { kind: 'cellref', ref: 'A1' },\n          right: { kind: 'cellref', ref: 'B1' },\n        },\n        right: { kind: 'number', value: 2 },\n      });\n    });\n\n    it('handles unary minus', () => {\n      const ast = parse('-A1');\n      expect(ast).toEqual({\n        kind: 'unary',\n        op: '-',\n        operand: { kind: 'cellref', ref: 'A1' },\n      });\n    });\n  });\n\n  describe('comparisons', () => {\n    it('parses greater than', () => {\n      const ast = parse('A1>30');\n      expect(ast).toEqual({\n        kind: 'binary',\n        op: '>',\n        left: { kind: 'cellref', ref: 'A1' },\n        right: { kind: 'number', value: 30 },\n      });\n    });\n\n    it('parses not equal', () => {\n      const ast = parse('A1<>B1');\n      expect(ast).toEqual({\n        kind: 'binary',\n        op: '<>',\n        left: { kind: 'cellref', ref: 'A1' },\n        right: { kind: 'cellref', ref: 'B1' },\n      });\n    });\n  });\n\n  describe('functions', () => {\n    it('parses SUM with range', () => {\n      const ast = parse('SUM(A1:A5)');\n      expect(ast).toEqual({\n        kind: 'function',\n        name: 'SUM',\n        args: [{ kind: 'range', start: 'A1', end: 'A5' }],\n      });\n    });\n\n    it('parses IF with three args', () => {\n      const ast = parse('IF(A1>30,\"big\",\"small\")');\n      expect(ast).toEqual({\n        kind: 'function',\n        name: 'IF',\n        args: [\n          { kind: 'binary', op: '>', left: { kind: 'cellref', ref: 'A1' }, right: { kind: 'number', value: 30 } },\n          { kind: 'string', value: 'big' },\n          { kind: 'string', value: 'small' },\n        ],\n      });\n    });\n\n    it('parses nested functions', () => {\n      const ast = parse('SUM(A1,MAX(B1:B3))');\n      expect(ast.kind).toBe('function');\n    });\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run tests to verify they fail**\n\nRun: `npx vitest run src/__tests__/parser.test.ts`\nExpected: FAIL — module not found.\n\n**Step 3: Implement the parser**\n\nCreate `src/parser.ts` with:\n\n1. A `tokenize(input: string): Token[]` function that scans input into tokens. Handles: numbers (int/float), strings (double-quoted), identifiers/booleans/cell-refs (letters+digits), operators (+, -, *, /, (, ), comma, colon, >, <, >=, <=, =, <>), whitespace (skip).\n   - To distinguish cell references from identifiers: if the token matches `/^[A-Z]+[0-9]+$/i`, it's a cell ref; if it matches `true`/`false` (case-insensitive), it's a boolean; otherwise it's an identifier.\n\n2. A recursive descent parser class with methods:\n   - `parse(): ASTNode` — entry point, calls `expression()`, checks EOF\n   - `expression(): ASTNode` — calls `comparison()`\n   - `comparison(): ASTNode` — calls `addition()`, loops on comparison operators\n   - `addition(): ASTNode` — calls `multiplication()`, loops on +/-\n   - `multiplication(): ASTNode` — calls `unary()`, loops on * and /\n   - `unary(): ASTNode` — handles unary minus, calls `primary()`\n   - `primary(): ASTNode` — handles Number, String, Boolean, CellRef (with range lookahead for colon), Identifier (function call), LParen (grouped expression)\n   - For function calls: consume identifier, LParen, parse args (each arg: try cell-ref + colon for range, else expression), RParen\n\n3. Export `function parse(input: string): ASTNode` that tokenizes and parses.\n4. Export `function extractCellRefs(node: ASTNode): Set<string>` that walks the AST and collects all cell reference strings (from CellRefNode and RangeNode — ranges expand to all cells in the rectangle).\n\nThe range expansion helper `expandRange(start: string, end: string): string[]` converts column letters to numbers, iterates the rectangle, converts back.\n\nColumn conversion helpers:\n- `colToNum(col: string): number` — A=0, B=1, ..., Z=25, AA=26, AB=27, etc.\n- `numToCol(num: number): string` — reverse of above\n- `parseCellRef(ref: string): { col: number; row: number }` — splits ref into column letters and row number\n- `formatCellRef(col: number, row: number): string` — formats back to string\n\n**Step 4: Run tests to verify they pass**\n\nRun: `npx vitest run src/__tests__/parser.test.ts`\nExpected: All tests PASS.\n\n**Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/parser.ts src/__tests__/parser.test.ts && git commit -m \"feat: add formula parser with tokenizer and recursive descent\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: Evaluator Module\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/evaluator.ts`\n- Create: `src/__tests__/evaluator.test.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 1, Task 2\n\n**Step 1: Write evaluator tests**\n\nCreate `src/__tests__/evaluator.test.ts`:\n\n```typescript\nimport { describe, it, expect } from 'vitest';\nimport { evaluate } from '../evaluator.js';\nimport { parse } from '../parser.js';\nimport type { CellValue } from '../types.js';\n\nfunction eval_(formula: string, cells: Record<string, CellValue> = {}): CellValue {\n  const ast = parse(formula);\n  return evaluate(ast, (ref) => cells[ref] ?? null);\n}\n\ndescribe('Evaluator', () => {\n  describe('literals', () => {\n    it('evaluates numbers', () => {\n      expect(eval_('42')).toBe(42);\n    });\n    it('evaluates strings', () => {\n      expect(eval_('\"hello\"')).toBe('hello');\n    });\n    it('evaluates booleans', () => {\n      expect(eval_('true')).toBe(true);\n    });\n  });\n\n  describe('arithmetic', () => {\n    it('adds', () => expect(eval_('2+3')).toBe(5));\n    it('subtracts', () => expect(eval_('10-4')).toBe(6));\n    it('multiplies', () => expect(eval_('3*4')).toBe(12));\n    it('divides', () => expect(eval_('10/4')).toBe(2.5));\n    it('handles precedence', () => expect(eval_('2+3*4')).toBe(14));\n    it('handles parentheses', () => expect(eval_('(2+3)*4')).toBe(20));\n    it('handles unary minus', () => expect(eval_('-5')).toBe(-5));\n  });\n\n  describe('cell references', () => {\n    it('resolves cell value', () => {\n      expect(eval_('A1', { A1: 10 })).toBe(10);\n    });\n    it('returns 0 for empty cell in arithmetic', () => {\n      expect(eval_('A1+1', {})).toBe(1);\n    });\n  });\n\n  describe('comparisons', () => {\n    it('greater than', () => expect(eval_('5>3')).toBe(true));\n    it('less than', () => expect(eval_('5<3')).toBe(false));\n    it('equal', () => expect(eval_('5=5')).toBe(true));\n    it('not equal', () => expect(eval_('5<>3')).toBe(true));\n    it('greater or equal', () => expect(eval_('5>=5')).toBe(true));\n    it('less or equal', () => expect(eval_('3<=5')).toBe(true));\n  });\n\n  describe('functions', () => {\n    const cells = { A1: 10, A2: 20, A3: 30 };\n\n    it('SUM', () => expect(eval_('SUM(A1:A3)', cells)).toBe(60));\n    it('AVERAGE', () => expect(eval_('AVERAGE(A1:A3)', cells)).toBe(20));\n    it('MIN', () => expect(eval_('MIN(A1:A3)', cells)).toBe(10));\n    it('MAX', () => expect(eval_('MAX(A1:A3)', cells)).toBe(30));\n    it('COUNT', () => expect(eval_('COUNT(A1:A3)', cells)).toBe(3));\n    it('IF true branch', () => expect(eval_('IF(A1>5,\"yes\",\"no\")', cells)).toBe('yes'));\n    it('IF false branch', () => expect(eval_('IF(A1>50,\"yes\",\"no\")', cells)).toBe('no'));\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run tests to verify they fail**\n\nRun: `npx vitest run src/__tests__/evaluator.test.ts`\nExpected: FAIL — module not found.\n\n**Step 3: Implement the evaluator**\n\nCreate `src/evaluator.ts`:\n\n```typescript\nexport function evaluate(node: ASTNode, lookup: (ref: string) => CellValue): CellValue\n```\n\nThe evaluator walks the AST recursively:\n\n- `NumberLiteral` → return `.value`\n- `StringLiteral` → return `.value`\n- `BooleanLiteral` → return `.value`\n- `CellRefNode` → return `lookup(node.ref)`\n- `UnaryOp` → evaluate operand, apply `-` (treat null as 0)\n- `BinaryOp` → evaluate left and right, apply operator\n  - For arithmetic (`+`, `-`, `*`, `/`): coerce to number (null → 0, boolean → 0/1, string → NaN)\n  - For comparisons: return boolean\n- `FunctionCall` → dispatch by name:\n  - For range-aggregate functions (SUM, AVERAGE, MIN, MAX, COUNT): expand range args via `expandRange`, lookup each cell, filter to numbers\n  - `SUM`: sum of numeric values\n  - `AVERAGE`: sum / count\n  - `MIN`: Math.min of numeric values\n  - `MAX`: Math.max of numeric values\n  - `COUNT`: count of numeric values\n  - `IF(condition, trueVal, falseVal)`: evaluate condition, if truthy evaluate and return trueVal, else falseVal\n- `RangeNode` → should only appear inside function calls; if evaluated standalone, throw error\n\nImport `expandRange` from `parser.ts`.\n\nHelper `toNumber(val: CellValue): number` — null→0, boolean→0/1, number→number, string→parseFloat (NaN if not numeric).\n\n**Step 4: Run tests to verify they pass**\n\nRun: `npx vitest run src/__tests__/evaluator.test.ts`\nExpected: All tests PASS.\n\n**Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/evaluator.ts src/__tests__/evaluator.test.ts && git commit -m \"feat: add AST evaluator with built-in functions\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 4: Spreadsheet Class\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/index.ts`\n- Create: `src/__tests__/spreadsheet.test.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 2, Task 3\n\n**Step 1: Write Spreadsheet tests**\n\nCreate `src/__tests__/spreadsheet.test.ts`:\n\n```typescript\nimport { describe, it, expect } from 'vitest';\nimport { Spreadsheet } from '../index.js';\n\ndescribe('Spreadsheet', () => {\n  describe('basic values', () => {\n    it('sets and gets a number', () => {\n      const s = new Spreadsheet();\n      s.set('A1', 42);\n      expect(s.get('A1')).toBe(42);\n    });\n\n    it('sets and gets a string', () => {\n      const s = new Spreadsheet();\n      s.set('A1', 'hello');\n      expect(s.get('A1')).toBe('hello');\n    });\n\n    it('sets and gets a boolean', () => {\n      const s = new Spreadsheet();\n      s.set('A1', true);\n      expect(s.get('A1')).toBe(true);\n    });\n\n    it('returns null for empty cells', () => {\n      const s = new Spreadsheet();\n      expect(s.get('A1')).toBeNull();\n    });\n  });\n\n  describe('formulas', () => {\n    it('evaluates simple formula', () => {\n      const s = new Spreadsheet();\n      s.set('A1', 10);\n      s.set('A2', 20);\n      s.set('A3', '=A1+A2');\n      expect(s.get('A3')).toBe(30);\n    });\n\n    it('evaluates formula with multiplication', () => {\n      const s = new Spreadsheet();\n      s.set('A1', 5);\n      s.set('A2', '=A1*3');\n      expect(s.get('A2')).toBe(15);\n    });\n  });\n\n  describe('reactive updates', () => {\n    it('updates dependents when source changes', () => {\n      const s = new Spreadsheet();\n      s.set('A1', 10);\n      s.set('A2', 20);\n      s.set('A3', '=A1+A2');\n      expect(s.get('A3')).toBe(30);\n\n      s.set('A1', 50);\n      expect(s.get('A3')).toBe(70);\n    });\n\n    it('updates transitive dependents', () => {\n      const s = new Spreadsheet();\n      s.set('A1', 5);\n      s.set('A2', '=A1*2');\n      s.set('A3', '=A2+1');\n      expect(s.get('A3')).toBe(11);\n\n      s.set('A1', 10);\n      expect(s.get('A2')).toBe(20);\n      expect(s.get('A3')).toBe(21);\n    });\n\n    it('handles diamond dependencies', () => {\n      const s = new Spreadsheet();\n      s.set('A1', 1);\n      s.set('B1', '=A1+1');\n      s.set('C1', '=A1+2');\n      s.set('D1', '=B1+C1');\n      expect(s.get('D1')).toBe(5);\n\n      s.set('A1', 10);\n      expect(s.get('D1')).toBe(23);\n    });\n  });\n\n  describe('built-in functions', () => {\n    it('SUM', () => {\n      const s = new Spreadsheet();\n      s.set('A1', 10);\n      s.set('A2', 20);\n      s.set('B1', '=SUM(A1:A2)');\n      expect(s.get('B1')).toBe(30);\n    });\n\n    it('AVERAGE', () => {\n      const s = new Spreadsheet();\n      s.set('A1', 10);\n      s.set('A2', 20);\n      s.set('B1', '=AVERAGE(A1:A2)');\n      expect(s.get('B1')).toBe(15);\n    });\n\n    it('MIN and MAX', () => {\n      const s = new Spreadsheet();\n      s.set('A1', 10);\n      s.set('A2', 20);\n      s.set('A3', 5);\n      expect(new Spreadsheet().set('A1', 10) === undefined || true); // just for setup\n      const s2 = new Spreadsheet();\n      s2.set('A1', 10);\n      s2.set('A2', 20);\n      s2.set('A3', 5);\n      s2.set('B1', '=MIN(A1:A3)');\n      s2.set('B2', '=MAX(A1:A3)');\n      expect(s2.get('B1')).toBe(5);\n      expect(s2.get('B2')).toBe(20);\n    });\n\n    it('COUNT', () => {\n      const s = new Spreadsheet();\n      s.set('A1', 10);\n      s.set('A2', 'hello');\n      s.set('A3', 30);\n      s.set('B1', '=COUNT(A1:A3)');\n      expect(s.get('B1')).toBe(2);\n    });\n\n    it('IF', () => {\n      const s = new Spreadsheet();\n      s.set('A1', 50);\n      s.set('C1', '=IF(A1>30,\"big\",\"small\")');\n      expect(s.get('C1')).toBe('big');\n\n      s.set('A1', 10);\n      expect(s.get('C1')).toBe('small');\n    });\n  });\n\n  describe('circular references', () => {\n    it('detects direct circular reference', () => {\n      const s = new Spreadsheet();\n      s.set('A1', '=B1');\n      expect(() => s.set('B1', '=A1')).toThrow();\n    });\n\n    it('detects self-reference', () => {\n      const s = new Spreadsheet();\n      expect(() => s.set('A1', '=A1')).toThrow();\n    });\n\n    it('detects indirect circular reference', () => {\n      const s = new Spreadsheet();\n      s.set('A1', '=B1');\n      s.set('B1', '=C1');\n      expect(() => s.set('C1', '=A1')).toThrow();\n    });\n\n    it('does not throw for valid dependencies', () => {\n      const s = new Spreadsheet();\n      s.set('A1', 10);\n      s.set('B1', '=A1');\n      s.set('C1', '=B1');\n      expect(s.get('C1')).toBe(10);\n    });\n  });\n\n  describe('getDisplay', () => {\n    it('displays numbers', () => {\n      const s = new Spreadsheet();\n      s.set('A1', 42);\n      expect(s.getDisplay('A1')).toBe('42');\n    });\n\n    it('displays strings', () => {\n      const s = new Spreadsheet();\n      s.set('A1', 'hello');\n      expect(s.getDisplay('A1')).toBe('hello');\n    });\n\n    it('displays booleans', () => {\n      const s = new Spreadsheet();\n      s.set('A1', true);\n      expect(s.getDisplay('A1')).toBe('TRUE');\n    });\n\n    it('displays empty cells', () => {\n      const s = new Spreadsheet();\n      expect(s.getDisplay('A1')).toBe('');\n    });\n\n    it('displays formula results', () => {\n      const s = new Spreadsheet();\n      s.set('A1', 10);\n      s.set('A2', 20);\n      s.set('A3', '=A1+A2');\n      expect(s.getDisplay('A3')).toBe('30');\n    });\n  });\n\n  describe('getCells', () => {\n    it('returns all non-empty cells', () => {\n      const s = new Spreadsheet();\n      s.set('A1', 10);\n      s.set('B1', '=A1*2');\n      const cells = s.getCells();\n      expect(cells.get('A1')).toBe(10);\n      expect(cells.get('B1')).toBe(20);\n      expect(cells.size).toBe(2);\n    });\n  });\n\n  describe('cell reference normalization', () => {\n    it('normalizes lowercase cell refs', () => {\n      const s = new Spreadsheet();\n      s.set('a1', 10);\n      expect(s.get('A1')).toBe(10);\n    });\n  });\n\n  describe('block ranges', () => {\n    it('SUM over a 2D block range', () => {\n      const s = new Spreadsheet();\n      s.set('A1', 1);\n      s.set('A2', 2);\n      s.set('B1', 3);\n      s.set('B2', 4);\n      s.set('C1', '=SUM(A1:B2)');\n      expect(s.get('C1')).toBe(10);\n    });\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run tests to verify they fail**\n\nRun: `npx vitest run src/__tests__/spreadsheet.test.ts`\nExpected: FAIL — module not found.\n\n**Step 3: Implement the Spreadsheet class**\n\nCreate `src/index.ts`:\n\n```typescript\nimport { parse, extractCellRefs } from './parser.js';\nimport { evaluate } from './evaluator.js';\nimport type { ASTNode, CellValue } from './types.js';\n\ninterface CellData {\n  rawValue: string | number | boolean;\n  formula: ASTNode | null;\n  computedValue: CellValue;\n  deps: Set<string>;       // cells this cell depends on\n}\n\nexport class Spreadsheet {\n  private cells = new Map<string, CellData>();\n  private reverseDeps = new Map<string, Set<string>>(); // cell → cells that depend on it\n\n  set(cell: string, value: string | number | boolean): void {\n    cell = cell.toUpperCase();\n\n    let formula: ASTNode | null = null;\n    let deps = new Set<string>();\n\n    // Parse formula if string starting with '='\n    if (typeof value === 'string' && value.startsWith('=')) {\n      const formulaStr = value.slice(1);\n      formula = parse(formulaStr);\n      deps = extractCellRefs(formula);\n    }\n\n    // Check for circular references before committing\n    if (deps.size > 0) {\n      this.checkCircular(cell, deps);\n    }\n\n    // Remove old reverse dependencies\n    const oldData = this.cells.get(cell);\n    if (oldData) {\n      for (const dep of oldData.deps) {\n        this.reverseDeps.get(dep)?.delete(cell);\n      }\n    }\n\n    // Add new reverse dependencies\n    for (const dep of deps) {\n      if (!this.reverseDeps.has(dep)) {\n        this.reverseDeps.set(dep, new Set());\n      }\n      this.reverseDeps.get(dep)!.add(cell);\n    }\n\n    // Compute value\n    const computedValue = formula\n      ? evaluate(formula, (ref) => this.cells.get(ref)?.computedValue ?? null)\n      : (value as CellValue);\n\n    this.cells.set(cell, { rawValue: value, formula, computedValue, deps });\n\n    // Recompute dependents in topological order\n    this.recomputeDependents(cell);\n  }\n\n  get(cell: string): CellValue {\n    cell = cell.toUpperCase();\n    return this.cells.get(cell)?.computedValue ?? null;\n  }\n\n  getDisplay(cell: string): string {\n    const val = this.get(cell);\n    if (val === null) return '';\n    if (typeof val === 'boolean') return val ? 'TRUE' : 'FALSE';\n    return String(val);\n  }\n\n  getCells(): Map<string, CellValue> {\n    const result = new Map<string, CellValue>();\n    for (const [ref, data] of this.cells) {\n      result.set(ref, data.computedValue);\n    }\n    return result;\n  }\n\n  private checkCircular(cell: string, deps: Set<string>): void {\n    // DFS from each dependency to see if we reach back to `cell`\n    const visited = new Set<string>();\n    const stack = [...deps];\n    while (stack.length > 0) {\n      const current = stack.pop()!;\n      if (current === cell) {\n        throw new Error(`Circular reference detected: ${cell}`);\n      }\n      if (visited.has(current)) continue;\n      visited.add(current);\n      const currentData = this.cells.get(current);\n      if (currentData) {\n        for (const dep of currentData.deps) {\n          stack.push(dep);\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  private recomputeDependents(changedCell: string): void {\n    // Topological sort of all dependents\n    const order = this.topoSort(changedCell);\n    for (const ref of order) {\n      const data = this.cells.get(ref);\n      if (data?.formula) {\n        data.computedValue = evaluate(data.formula, (r) => this.cells.get(r)?.computedValue ?? null);\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  private topoSort(startCell: string): string[] {\n    const visited = new Set<string>();\n    const result: string[] = [];\n\n    const visit = (cell: string) => {\n      if (visited.has(cell)) return;\n      visited.add(cell);\n      const dependents = this.reverseDeps.get(cell);\n      if (dependents) {\n        for (const dep of dependents) {\n          visit(dep);\n        }\n      }\n      result.push(cell);\n    };\n\n    visit(startCell);\n    // Remove startCell itself from results, reverse for correct order\n    return result.filter((c) => c !== startCell).reverse();\n  }\n}\n```\n\nNote: The topological sort uses post-order DFS on reverse deps, then reverses — this ensures a cell is recomputed only after all cells it depends on have been recomputed.\n\n**Step 4: Run tests to verify they pass**\n\nRun: `npx vitest run src/__tests__/spreadsheet.test.ts`\nExpected: All tests PASS.\n\n**Step 5: Run all tests**\n\nRun: `npx vitest run`\nExpected: All test suites PASS.\n\n**Step 6: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/index.ts src/__tests__/spreadsheet.test.ts && git commit -m \"feat: add Spreadsheet class with reactive updates and circular reference detection\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 5: Final Verification\n\n**Files:** none (verification only)\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 4\n\n**Step 1: Run full test suite**\n\nRun: `npx vitest run`\nExpected: All tests PASS.\n\n**Step 2: Type check**\n\nRun: `npx tsc --noEmit`\nExpected: No errors.\n\n**Step 3: Lint**\n\nRun: `npx eslint src/`\nExpected: No errors (or only warnings).\n\n**Step 4: Final commit if needed**\n\nFix any issues found, commit fixes.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"